item.title: Black Ops Commercial Spot: Kobe & Kimmel "There is a Soldier in All of Us"
item.description:
Black Ops Commercial Spot: Kobe & Kimmel "There is a Soldier in All of Us"
The first commercial for Call of Duty: Black Ops Yes, that's Kobe Bryant and Jimmy Kimmel firing off military-grade weaponry with their callsigns written on them ("Mamba" and "Proud n00b" respectively, in case you missed them) — a clear nod to the ability for players to put their own logos on their weapons in Black Ops. I suspect this will cause controversy — some people will say "you're glorifying violence" and other people will see it as "I guess we never grow out of playing army men." It's clearly a fantasy spot and I don't have a problem with it — it made me smile. And again, love that soundtrack. Add your thoughts below...
